name: Cocoon
description:
In solitude
Between laughters and cries
Here I lie
Mind goes brute

Their wings are open
Freed and seen
Behold, dear maiden
I will someday win

Days are gone
But I counted the seconds
Not the moon nor the sun
Cares for my frown

Emerge, at last
And out of the cocoon
To the sky, I blast
But the dew made me drown.
